Thayer Central is requiring tickets for entry into the volleyball game. You must have a ticket and pay admission in order to get in. post_text:
Tri County Public Schools Custodial Position Available

Tri County Public Schools is taking applications for an evening custodian for our school district. The hours for the position during the school year are 1:00 P.M.-10:30 P.M. with some weekends scheduled for student activities. Summer hours are 6:00 AM-4:30 PM M-Th and 6:00 AM-11:00 AM on Friday. Tri County pays an excellent wage for custodians and provides health insurance and other benefits for our full time staff members. Custodians must meet all local, state, and federal guidelines to be employed by Tri County. Interested persons should contact the Tri County District Office (402-683-2037) or go to www.tricountyschools.org under the district tab for more information about the district, a job description, and an application. Tri County Public Schools is an equal opportunity employer.

post_text: Tri County will be honoring our 2020 seniors as well as all of our athletes who would be participating in this year's spring sports. A beacon of light ceremony is scheduled for Wednesday, April 20th, at 8:20 PM to support all students who have been impacted by their school's closure. Schools from across the state of Nebraska have been conducting ceremonies such as these. Supporters can participate by turning on their outside lights at their homes from 8:20 to 8:40 PM. Tri County will turn the Football lights for 20 minutes beginning at 8:20 PM. Please follow the CDC guidelines for social distancing. Patrons or students should not gather at the stadium or any other place. If you want to see the stadium lights you'll have to parade by the football field that night during the 20 minutes. I just want to make sure we are following the guidelines. Again, no gathering allowed.
text: Tri County will be honoring our 2020 seniors as well as all of our athletes who would be participating in this year's spring sports. A beacon of light ceremony is scheduled for Wednesday, April 20th, at 8:20 PM to support all students who have been impacted by their school's closure. Schools from across the state of Nebraska have been conducting ceremonies such as these. Supporters can participate by turning on their outside lights at their homes from 8:20 to 8:40 PM. Tri County will turn the Football lights for 20 minutes beginning at 8:20 PM. Please follow the CDC guidelines for social distancing. Patrons or students should not gather at the stadium or any other place. If you want to see the stadium lights you'll have to parade by the football field that night during the 20 minutes. I just want to make sure we are following the guidelines. Again, no gathering allowed.

post_text: On Thursday, all Tri County 4th, 5th, and 6th graders attended the Young People’s Concert presented by the Lincoln Symphony Orchestra. Hundreds of students from Lincoln and other areas of the state filled the Lied Center for Performing Arts in downtown Lincoln to hear the orchestra play “The Composer Is Dead.” During music class on the days prior to the trip, students read the Lemony Snicket picture book with the same title and then had the opportunity to hear Nathaniel Stookey’s composition Thursday morning. Thank you to the Tri County PTO for making this experience possible for our students by purchasing our tickets!!

post_text:
TRI COUNTY PUBLIC SCHOOLS

Food Service Position

Tri County Public Schools is taking applications for a position in the cafeteria preparing meals for students. The position is approximately 30 hours per week, depending on the baking and menu for the day. The hours per day could fluctuate from 5 to 7 hours per day. The staff member will work with five other cafeteria works in planning, preparing, serving, and cleaning the kitchen on a daily basis. Benefits include twelve month single health insurance and single dental insurance that are fully paid by the district. Interested persons should contact the Tri County District Office (402-683-2037) for an application or go to the school website at www.tricountyschools.org to find our school application. Tri County is an Equal Opportunity Employer.
